{"title":"Install anaconda","date":"2021-02-23T12:51:53.000Z","date_formatted":{"ll":"Feb 23, 2021","L":"02/23/2021","MM-DD":"02-23"},"link":"2021/02/23/Install anaconda","comments":true,"tags":["Anaconda"],"updated":"2021-02-23T12:51:53.000Z","content":"<h1 id=\"installing-anaconda-and-pip-for-an-ubuntu-system\">Installing anaconda and pip for an ubuntu system<a title=\"#installing-anaconda-and-pip-for-an-ubuntu-system\" href=\"#installing-anaconda-and-pip-for-an-ubuntu-system\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"1-installing-anaconda\">1 Installing anaconda<a title=\"#1-installing-anaconda\" href=\"#1-installing-anaconda\"></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"1.1-download-the-package-of-it\">1.1 Download the package of it<a title=\"#1.1-download-the-package-of-it\" href=\"#1.1-download-the-package-of-it\"></a></h3>\n<figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">wget https://repo.anaconda.com/archive/Anaconda3-2019.07-Linux-x86_64.sh</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n<h3 id=\"1.2-installing-it(default)\">1.2 Installing it(default)<a title=\"#1.2-installing-it(default)\" href=\"#1.2-installing-it(default)\"></a></h3>\n<figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">bash Anaconda3-2019.07-Linux-x86_64.sh</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n<h3 id=\"1.3-load-the-environment-variables\">1.3 Load the environment variables<a title=\"#1.3-load-the-environment-variables\" href=\"#1.3-load-the-environment-variables\"></a></h3>\n<figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># if not an root user</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"built_in\">source</span> ~/.bashrc</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># if root user</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"built_in\">echo</span> <span class=\"string\">&#x27;export PATH=&quot;/root/anaconda3/bin:$PATH&quot;&#x27;</span> &gt;&gt; ~/.bashrc</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"built_in\">source</span> ~/.bashrc</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n<h2 id=\"2-installing-pip\">2 Installing pip<a title=\"#2-installing-pip\" href=\"#2-installing-pip\"></a></h2>\n<figure class=\"highlight bash\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br><span class=\"line\">8</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># 1 update the packages of system</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">sudo apt-get update</span><br><span class=\"line\">sudo apt-get upgrade</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># 2 install pip</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">sudo apt-get install python-pip</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\"># 3 check if it was installed successful</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n","prev":{"title":"The Art of Software Testing","link":"2021/07/31/The-Art-of-Software-Testing"},"next":{"title":"Image similarity","link":"2020/12/27/Image similarity"},"plink":"http://thswind.github.io/2021/02/23/Install anaconda/","toc":[{"id":"installing-anaconda-and-pip-for-an-ubuntu-system","title":"Installing anaconda and pip for an ubuntu system","index":"1","children":[{"id":"1-installing-anaconda","title":"1 Installing anaconda","index":"1.1","children":[{"id":"1.1-download-the-package-of-it","title":"1.1 Download the package of it","index":"1.1.1"},{"id":"1.2-installing-it(default)","title":"1.2 Installing it(default)","index":"1.1.2"},{"id":"1.3-load-the-environment-variables","title":"1.3 Load the environment variables","index":"1.1.3"}]},{"id":"2-installing-pip","title":"2 Installing pip","index":"1.2"}]}],"reward":true,"copyright":{"author":"THSWind","link":"<a href=\"http://thswind.github.io/2021/02/23/Install anaconda/\" title=\"Install anaconda\">http://thswind.github.io/2021/02/23/Install anaconda/</a>","license":"Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International (<a href=\\\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/\\\" rel=\\\"external nofollow\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">CC BY-NC-ND 4.0</a>)"},"reading_time":"116 words in 1 min"}